<TITLE> DU exams deferred </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 28 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka University authorities have deferred all examinations scheduled for Mar. 1 and 2. A fresh schedule for the deferred examinations will be announced later, said DU public relations department director Ashraf Ali Khan on Saturday. Dhaka University was flying the national flag at half mast in mourning for the deaths of army officers and civilians in the BDR mutiny. Students of Awami League-backed Chhatra League and BNP-backed Chhatra Dal wore black badges to observe the national mourning. Dhaka Medical College's BCL unit held a silent procession on campus. bdnews24.com/jf/m
